---
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Undergraduate Research - Xi Lin</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 sm:px-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900">Back to home</a>
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Undergraduate Research</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
        My undergraduate stage was centered on perception, robotic vision, and research prototyping. It included CNN-based robotic object detection, UAV-oriented visual navigation integration, and early trajectory modeling work in lab settings.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-gray-200">
        <img src="/assets/projects/undergrad-trajectory.png" alt="Trajectory modeling result" class="w-full object-cover" />
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">CNN-Based Robotic Object Detection</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            Improved YOLOv5 with adaptive convolution and multi-scale training, then connected detection outputs with VINS-Fusion for visual navigation and obstacle-avoidance-oriented robotic tasks.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Trajectory Modeling at JHU</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            Built dynamics forecasting pipelines with LSTM and Gaussian-mixture-based data generation for robot trajectory analysis and motion prediction in dynamic environments.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
